**Loan eligibility** is determined by your Fixed Obligation to Income Ratio (FOIR) — most banks cap total EMIs at 40–50% of net monthly income. For a ₹1 lakh salary with no existing EMIs, you may be eligible for a home loan of ₹50–60 lakh at 8.5% for 20 years. This calculator computes your maximum loan amount based on income and existing obligations.
